    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="111"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d111">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="from"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> to <gloss target="#t_Generalissimo1"
                            >Generalissimo</gloss>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CKS1" type="to">Chiang</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d111fn1">Channel of transmission not indicated.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-10">November 10,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Personal and most secret from the President to the <gloss
                        target="#t_Generalissimo1">Generalissimo</gloss>
                </p>
                <p>I am terribly sorry to learn of Madame <persName corresp="#p_CMlS1"
                        >Chiang</persName>’s illness<note n="2" xml:id="d111fn2">See <persName
                            corresp="#p_CKS1">Chiang</persName>’s telegram of November 9, 1943, to
                            <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName>, <hi rend="italic"
                            >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_73">p. 73</ref>.</note> and sincerely hope
                    that she will be fully recovered in time for our conference.</p>
                <p>I have had a long talk with General <persName corresp="#p_SBB1"
                        >Somervell</persName> and appreciate very much your courtesies to him. He
                    has given me your private message<note n="3" xml:id="d111fn3">See <persName
                            corresp="#p_SBB1">Somervell</persName>’s memorandum of October 30, 1943,
                            <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_56">p. 56</ref>.</note> as
                    I have already indicated to you.<note n="4" xml:id="d111fn4">See <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_72">p. 72</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I agree with you fully that we should meet together before I see <persName
                        corresp="#p_SIV1">Stalin</persName>. I want so much to have some good talks
                    with you so, naturally, I am eagerly looking forward to seeing you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
